# Embedded Linux Lab

My hands-on journey to become strong in Embedded Linux by the end of this year.

## Goal

Build real experience in:

- Embedded Linux fundamentals
- Linux command line and system administration
- GPIO / UART / SPI / I2C basics
- Cross-compiling applications for ARM
- Buildroot
- Yocto
- Docker on embedded Linux
- Debugging and performance analysis
- End-to-end embedded projects

Target: study and practice **10 hours per week** and finish the year with a strong practical portfolio.

## Current Setup

- Board: Raspberry Pi 3
- OS: Ubuntu 22.04 64-bit
- SSH: `192.168.0.50`

## Available Hardware

- Raspberry Pi 3
- 8-channel logic analyzer
- Arduino board
- STM32 Discovery board
- LEDs
- 7-segment display
- Potentiometers
- Bluetooth module
- DHT sensor
- Motor speed encoder
- LDR light sensor

## Why This Repo Exists

This repo is my engineering notebook and project archive.

I will use it to store:

- weekly notes
- commands that worked
- errors and fixes
- wiring notes
- boot logs
- project code
- experiment results
- photos and screenshots
- lessons learned

By the end of the year, this repo should show clear progress from beginner to capable embedded Linux developer.

## Learning Strategy

I will learn in stages:

1. Linux basics on Raspberry Pi
2. GPIO and simple hardware control
3. Serial communication with Arduino / STM32
4. Sensor integration
5. Logic analyzer usage for debugging
6. Cross-compiling C/C++ programs
7. Custom Linux images with Buildroot
8. Embedded Linux development with Yocto
9. Docker on ARM / embedded Linux
10. Debugging, tracing, and performance tuning
11. Final capstone project

